T*
(1. INTENDED USE) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(DermaRash is a consumer, AI-assisted EDUCATIONAL application that allows a) Tj
T*
(user to learn about general skin-appearance information that visually) Tj
T*
(resembles a photo they have captured of themselves. All output is) Tj
T*
(informational and backed by citations to authoritative public health and) Tj
T*
(dermatology sources \(American Academy of Dermatology, National Health) Tj
T*
(Service UK, Mayo Clinic, DermNet NZ, NIH MedlinePlus, World Health) Tj
T*
(Organization\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. NOT A MEDICAL DEVICE - BASIS OF SELF-CLASSIFICATION) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(DermaRash does not diagnose, cure, mitigate, prevent, or treat any) Tj
T*
(disease. It does not recommend, prescribe, or adjust medication, dosage,) Tj
T*
(or any form of clinical treatment. It does not perform clinical) Tj
T*
(measurement or provide care-routing decisions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2.1 United States - FDA 21 CFR 880 / General Wellness Guidance) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    \(FDA, "General Wellness: Policy for Low-Risk Devices", Sept 2019\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    DermaRash meets the criteria for a General Wellness product:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(      \(a\) its intended use relates to maintaining or encouraging a) Tj
T*
(          general state of health or a healthy activity \(general) Tj
T*
(          awareness of skin appearance and public-source education\);) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(      \(b\) it does not present inherent risk to a user's safety when used) Tj
T*
(          as intended, because it provides educational information only,) Tj
T*
(          carries a mandatory educational notice in the product, and is) Tj
T*
(          limited to visual reference notes and public-source reading) Tj
T*
(          links;) Tj
ET
endstream
