(3. RISK CONTROLS EMBEDDED IN THE PRODUCT) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  \(a\) Mandatory consent screen before any data submission, disclosing) Tj
T*
(      what data is sent, to whom, and how it is used.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  \(b\) Non-diagnostic terminology throughout the application \(e.g.) Tj
T*
(      "Visible Features Summary", "Visible Feature Notes", "Public) Tj
T*
(      Reading Links"\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  \(c\) Educational banner and app notice on every report.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  \(d\) Hard AI guardrails in all three supported languages forbidding) Tj
T*
(      diagnosis, prescription, dosage, and definitive clinical language.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  \(e\) Curated public-source links shown with each report.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  \(f\) No diagnosis, treatment, prescription, or care-routing language in the) Tj
T*
(      user-facing output.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. DATA HANDLING) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(DermaRash does not use any third-party AI service. AI inference runs on) Tj
T*
(self-hosted infrastructure operated by the developer at) Tj
T*
(derma.idakim.net. User data is not used to train AI models, is not) Tj
T*
(sold, and is not shared with advertisers. Full disclosure is available) Tj
